Name: AccountCurrencyCode
Notes: The currency of the Customer account.

Name: AccountDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer account.

Name: AccountTimeZoneId
Notes: Name of the timezone selected for the Customer account. For example: "(GMT-05:00) Eastern Time". This field does not reflect the current state of daylight saving time for the timezone.

Name: AdFormat
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
TEXT / text
IMAGE / image
DYNAMIC_IMAGE / dynamic_image
FLASH / flash
VIDEO / video
HTML / html
AUDIO / audio
COMPOSITE / composite
PRINT / print
Notes: The ad type.

Name: AdGroupId
Notes: The ID of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupName
Notes: The name of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: Status of the ad group.

Name: AdNetworkType1
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Search Network
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: First level network type.

Name: AdNetworkType2
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Google search
SEARCH_PARTNERS / Search partners
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: Second level network type (includes search partners).

Name: AllConversionRate
Notes: AllConversions divided by total clicks that can be conversion-tracked. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: AllConversions
Notes: Best estimate of the total number of conversions that AdWords drives. Includes website, cross-device, and phone call conversions.

Name: AllConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all of your conversions, including those that are estimated.

Name: AverageCost
Notes: The average amount you pay per interaction. This amount is the total cost of your ads divided by the total number of interactions.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpe
Notes: The average amount that you’ve been charged for an ad engagement. This amount is the total cost of all ad engagements divided by the total number of ad engagements.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: AverageCpv
Notes: The average amount you pay each time someone views your ad. The average CPV is defined by the total cost of all ad views divided by the number of views.

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers.

Name: CampaignId
Notes: The ID of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignName
Notes: The name of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: The status of the Campaign.

Name: ClickConversionRate
Notes: The number of converted clicks divided by your total clicks that can be tracked to a conversion. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: ConversionCategoryName
Notes: A category that describes the action the user will take to complete a conversion. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned. Values: "Download", "Lead", "Purchase/Sale", "Signup", "View of a key page", and "Other".

Name: ConversionRate
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: Conversions
Notes: The number of conversions for all conversion actions that you have opted into optimization.

Name: ConversionTrackerId
Notes: ID of the conversion tracker.

Name: ConversionTypeName
Notes: The name of the conversion type. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions.

Name: ConvertedClicks
Notes: The number of clicks that converted within your chosen conversion window.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period.

Name: CostPerAllConversion
Notes: Total cost divided by all conversions.

Name: CostPerConversion
Notes: Total cost divided by total ConversionValue.

Name: CostPerConvertedClick
Notes: Cost divided by your total converted clicks.

Name: CreativeId
Notes: ID of the ad.

Name: CrossDeviceConversions
Notes: Conversions from when a customer clicks on an AdWords ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in your AllConversions column.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: CustomerDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: DayOfWeek
Enum Values:
MONDAY / Monday
TUESDAY / Tuesday
WEDNESDAY / Wednesday
THURSDAY / Thursday
FRIDAY / Friday
SATURDAY / Saturday
SUNDAY / Sunday
Notes: The name of the day of the week, e.g., "Monday".

Name: DestinationUrl
Notes: Destination URL for the impression.

Name: Device
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other
DESKTOP / Computers
HIGH_END_MOBILE / Mobile devices with full browsers
TABLET / Tablets with full browsers
Notes: Device type where the impression was shown.

Name: EngagementRate
Notes: How often people engage with your ad after it's shown to them. This is the number of ad expansions divided by the number of times your ad is shown. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: Engagements
Notes: The number of engagements. An engagement occurs when a viewer expands your Lightbox ad. Also, in the future, other ad types may support engagement metrics.

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: FinalUrl
Notes: Final URL of the impressions.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: InteractionRate
Notes: How often people interact with your ad after it is shown to them. This is the number of interactions divided by the number of times your ad is shown. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: Interactions
Notes: The number of interactions. An interaction is the main user action associated with an ad format—clicks for text and shopping ads, views for video ads, and so on.

Name: KeywordId
Notes: The ID of the Keyword that triggered the ad.

Name: KeywordTextMatchingQuery
Notes: Keyword that matched the query and triggered the ad.

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: MonthOfYear
Enum Values:
JANUARY / January
FEBRUARY / February
MARCH / March
APRIL / April
MAY / May
JUNE / June
JULY / July
AUGUST / August
SEPTEMBER / September
OCTOBER / October
NOVEMBER / November
DECEMBER / December
Notes: The name of the month of the year, e.g., "December".

Name: PrimaryCompanyName
Notes: Company name of the account.

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: Query
Notes: If the string for this attribute is longer than 128 char bytes, the returned result will NOT be a single aggregated row.

Name: QueryMatchTypeWithVariant
Enum Values:
AUTO / auto
BROAD / broad
EXACT / exact
EXPANDED / broad
PHRASE / phrase
NEAR_EXACT / exact (close variant)
NEAR_PHRASE / phrase (close variant)
Notes: Match type of the keyword that triggered the ad, including variants. See https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/2472708 for an explanation of close variants.

Name: TrackingUrlTemplate
Notes: Tracking template of the main object of this row.

Name: ValuePerAllConversion
Notes: The value, on average, of all conversions.

Name: ValuePerConversion
Notes: The total value of your conversions divided by the total number of converted clicks.

Name: ValuePerConvertedClick
Notes: The total value of all conversions divided by the total number of converted clicks.

Name: VideoQuartile100Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched all of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: VideoQuartile25Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 25% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: VideoQuartile50Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 50% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: VideoQuartile75Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 75% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: VideoViewRate
Notes: The number of views your TrueView video ad receives divided by its number of impressions, including thumbnail impressions for TrueView in-display ads. Percentage returned as "x.xx%".

Name: VideoViews
Notes: The number of times your video ads were viewed.

Name: ViewThroughConversions
Notes: The total number of view-through conversions. These happen when a customer sees an image or rich media ad, then later completes a conversion on your site without interacting with (e.g. clicking on) another ad.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
